Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @Zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce}(thinly sliced) (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}(halved). Mince @Chives{¼%ounce}(minced). Quarter @Lemon{1}(quartered).

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a medium #bowl. Wipe out pan.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water; pat dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add shrimp or sausage; cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, 3-5 minutes for shrimp or 4-6 minutes for sausage. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl with zucchini. Wash out pan.

> Use pan used for shrimp or sausage here.

Once water is boiling, add @Penne Pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While penne cooks, heat @Butter{½%tablespoon} and a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add tomatoes and season with @Italian Seasoning{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. (Use the rest of the Italian Seasoning as you like.) Cook, stirring, until tomatoes are softened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in half the chives and juice from half the lemon.

Reduce heat to low, then stir in @Mushroom Stock Concentrate{1} and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water.

Whisk in @Crème Fraîche{4%tablespoon}; season with salt and pepper.

Add zucchini, mushrooms, and drained penne to pan with sauce; stir to combine. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. TIP: If needed, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls. Sprinkle with @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon} and remaining chives. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Serve shrimp or sausage atop pasta.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.